tldr: The sleep questionnaire application was reviewed against its
  specifications, and several key missing features were implemented. This
  included adding a tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, detecting and
  providing recommendations for COMISA and insufficient sleep syndrome, and
  integrating external resource links into the reports.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to verify adherence to the provided statement of work and detailed
  specifications. The review highlighted critical missing functionalities, such
  as a granular tiredness severity scale, specific detection for COMISA
  (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea), and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, as well
  as the absence of external resource links in the generated reports. The
  subsequent implementation phase successfully addressed these high-priority
  items. A 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings for
  high scores, was integrated into the questionnaire UI and reflected in both
  the web and PDF reports. Advanced detection logic and tailored recommendations
  for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome were added to enhance diagnostic
  capabilities. Furthermore, a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps" section,
  featuring placeholder outbound links to various sleep and mental health
  organizations, was incorporated into the reports, significantly improving the
  application's ability to provide comprehensive guidance and support to users.
